{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But, on the other hand, if you take into account that the community paid its rabbi, its hazzan, its Talmud Torah, its mikveh, its kashrut, all from the money which was paid and contributed by the individual members according to their financial status, it was only right that everybody should take their part.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father was very jolly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was an [INAUDIBLE] man.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Used to say, my customers never complain, [LAUGHS] meaning that  the dead don't complain.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was an unpleasant task, but being a communally inclined family, one has got to accept sometime unpleasant tasks, which was totally unpaid for.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was purely on an honorary basis.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And probably it brought only more animosity than friends.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But, on the other hand, the communal atmosphere was such that people understood that things were done genuinely for communal methods and not for personal gain.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A, we didn't need it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And only people who were in relatively good financial circumstances could accept that position, because otherwise they would have been put under pressure that, look, if you do that to me, I'm not going to buy from you, and all that.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now my father, having been in the real estate business, when anybody wanted to have a house built for themselves or wanted to rent a property, it wasn't through-- and, presumably, the majority of the customers were non-Jewish, anyway.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He wasn't in-- in need of the Jewish custom next morning whether they buy the fruits and bread and whatnots from us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, that brings me to the Jewish communal life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There were two Jewish bakeries.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we lived in the nice part of the town, which was starting on the bottom of the Alps.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
